## FRONTEND REQUIREMENT

**Frontend must send thread_id back on confirm turn for this to work end-to-end.**

The checkpointer stores state (including `pending_mrr_data`) keyed by `thread_id`. If the frontend generates a new `thread_id` on the confirm turn, the checkpointer loads empty state and `pending_mrr_data` is `None`, causing the submit to fail with "No MRR data to submit."

The frontend should:
1. Capture `thread_id` from the `meta` SSE event (emitted on the preview turn).
2. Resend that same `thread_id` in subsequent messages (confirm/cancel).

Without this, the confirm/cancel flow will not work end-to-end, though the app will not crash.

